  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Leveraging EITI and PIAC reports for anti-corruption reforms in Ghana&#x2019;s Extractive sector</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.Hold project inception meeting to discuss implementation arrangements for the project;
2.Commission research into typology and nature of corruption risks in Ghana extractive sector;
3.Validate research findings;
4.Launch research report;
5.Distribute report to key stakeholders;
6.Organise radio and T.V. interviews on the findings and recommendations of the report;
7.Develop policy briefs;
8.Organise policy roundtable with key sector agencies on the findings and recommendations of the report;
9.Organise policy roundtable with relevant Parliamentary Committees on the findings and recommendations of the report;
10.Organise a briefing session for key anti-corruption bodies;
11.Collaborate with the Ghana Anti-Corruption Campaign Coalition to prosecute a media campaign on corruption risks in the extractive sector and how to combat them.
12.Review government&#x2019;s responsiveness to demands of the project and its related campaign.
13.Pilot mineral revenue tracking in four mining host distrcts;
14.Track ABFA-funded projects in 6 frontline oil and gas districts.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The key results that will be achieved over the project period are:

1.     Establishing the typology and forms of corruption in the extractive sector;

2.     Creating awareness of relevant state agencies of corruption risks in the extractive sector;

3.     Mobilising citizens for reforms to reduce the corruption risks in the extractive sector;

4.     Achieving a reduction in the level of corruption risks through reforms in the sector.</narrative>
  </description>
